## Workflow Rules

1. Before starting any task, check `conductor/tracks/` for existing work
2. Each agent writes output to their section in the track file
3. Do not skip phases — each agent's output is the next agent's input
4. Mark track status: `pending → in-progress → review → done`
5. Code review required before `done`

---

## Agent Activation Guide

| Trigger | Command | Agent | Model |
|---------|---------|-------|-------|
| New feature/bug | `/agent-team init "<description>"` | BA | Opus (critical) |
| Schema work | `/agent-team db <track-id>` | DB Engineer | Sonnet |
| API/backend work | `/agent-team backend <track-id>` | Backend Dev | Sonnet |
| UI/frontend work | `/agent-team frontend <track-id>` | Frontend Dev | Sonnet |
| AI integration | `/agent-team ai <track-id>` | AI Engineer | Sonnet |
| Parallel (DB + FE) | `/agent-team parallel db frontend <track-id>` | Both | Sonnet |
| Review | `/agent-team review <track-id>` | Code Reviewer | Opus (critical) |
| Status check | `/agent-team status` | — | — |

**Native agents:** `.claude/agents/` — auto-detected by Claude Code, no manual paste needed
**Accumulated knowledge:** `conductor/knowledge.md` — lessons learned across tracks
